WEBVTT

00:01.366 --> 00:02.734
I'm here because
I want you to come home.

00:02.735 --> 00:03.525
Back to the firm?

00:03.526 --> 00:04.673
Yes, and not only that,

00:04.674 --> 00:05.955
you can get the ten
best associates

00:05.955 --> 00:07.630
from Robert Zane's
stable to come with you.

00:07.631 --> 00:08.939
And what's in this for me?

00:08.940 --> 00:10.906
I'll make sure that you are
the youngest senior partner

00:10.907 --> 00:11.705
we've ever had.

00:11.706 --> 00:14.311
As of this morning,
we're merging with Robert Zane.

00:14.312 --> 00:15.624
When I came over,
you said my name

00:15.625 --> 00:16.958
would be the
one to go up next.

00:16.960 --> 00:17.859
You have my word.

00:17.861 --> 00:19.260
Your name goes up next.

00:19.262 --> 00:21.095
Alex, what are you doing?

00:21.097 --> 00:22.730
I'm going through every one
of Samantha Wheeler's files,

00:22.732 --> 00:24.765
'cause a fight's coming,
and I'm gonna be ready.

00:24.767 --> 00:27.068
Katrina, are you sure
you're gonna be okay

00:27.070 --> 00:28.936
firing people
you've worked with for years?

00:28.938 --> 00:30.004
I'll tell you
what I told Louis,

00:30.006 --> 00:32.006
that if I'm going to grow
in my role here,

00:32.008 --> 00:33.808
this is something I'm going
to have to learn to do.

00:33.810 --> 00:36.043
I gave you an order,
and you blatantly ignored me.

00:36.045 --> 00:38.045
I did do what you
originally asked:

00:38.047 --> 00:40.092
to objectively evaluate
the associates.

00:40.093 --> 00:42.226
I don't care.
Brian is staying.

00:42.228 --> 00:44.929
Gavin Andrews is a hell of a
lot more than meets the eye.

00:44.931 --> 00:47.799
And a guy with your history
would want to be more careful

00:47.801 --> 00:49.867
about who he gets
into bed with.

00:49.869 --> 00:50.902
Tell me what
you're talking about,

00:50.904 --> 00:53.237
or get out
of my goddamn office.

00:53.239 --> 00:55.707
I admit I'm starting to see
what you see in her.

00:55.709 --> 00:57.075
That's all I was hoping for.

00:57.077 --> 00:58.743
Now I can tell you
why I was hoping it.

00:58.745 --> 01:00.144
What haven't you told me?

01:00.146 --> 01:01.879
Her name goes
up on the wall next.

01:05.051 --> 01:06.641
I mean,
how was I supposed to know

01:06.642 --> 01:07.841
she was married?
- I don't know,

01:07.843 --> 01:09.676
maybe her wedding ring
could have tipped you off.

01:09.678 --> 01:10.844
Mm.

01:10.846 --> 01:13.313
I was 23, you know?

01:13.315 --> 01:15.015
I wasn't looking
at no damn rings.

01:15.017 --> 01:17.484
You really had some balls
when you were younger.

01:17.486 --> 01:19.920
Still do,
thank you very much.

01:19.922 --> 01:22.322
Now, why don't you get to it?

01:22.324 --> 01:24.958
- Why don't I get to what?
- Harvey, you've got plenty

01:24.960 --> 01:28.228
of friends to have drinks with,
most of them prettier than me.

01:28.230 --> 01:29.663
You've got something
on your mind.

01:29.665 --> 01:32.232
Let's hear it.
- Robert, do you remember

01:32.234 --> 01:33.934
when you told me
you promised Samantha

01:33.936 --> 01:35.769
her name would go up next?
- I do.

01:35.771 --> 01:39.406
I made Alex the same promise.

01:39.408 --> 01:42.509
- Why you telling me now?
- Because we're partners.

01:42.511 --> 01:46.646
I don't want to keep
any secrets from my partner.

01:46.648 --> 01:49.182
Then I guess there's only
one thing to do.

01:49.184 --> 01:51.685
- What's that?
- Kick the can down the road.

01:51.687 --> 01:53.854
Because there's no way
both of us are gonna be able

01:53.856 --> 01:56.123
to keep that promise,
and for all we know,

01:56.125 --> 01:58.825
one of them could get hit
by a bus before we have

01:58.827 --> 02:00.627
to make that call.
- Then I guess

02:00.629 --> 02:01.962
it's a good thing
both our names

02:01.964 --> 02:05.165
are already up there.
- Sure is.

02:05.167 --> 02:08.368
- Another drink?
- Yeah, make it a double.

02:08.370 --> 02:10.270
And where are you going?

02:10.271 --> 02:13.740
To make room for that double.

02:15.110 --> 02:16.343
Excuse me, would you mind
giving me a minute to...?

02:16.345 --> 02:19.880
Oh, I'm so sorry, I--
I didn't hear you come in.

02:19.882 --> 02:23.283
Um, I'll just go.
- Are you all right?

02:23.285 --> 02:24.885
Uh, yeah.

02:24.887 --> 02:27.988
I, um--I just got a phone call.

02:27.990 --> 02:30.390
Um, it's not important.

02:30.392 --> 02:32.526
Excuse me.
- No, you stay.

02:32.528 --> 02:34.361
I'll use the one downstairs.

02:34.363 --> 02:37.364
Take as long as you need.

02:37.366 --> 02:40.901
For what it's worth...

02:40.903 --> 02:43.236
I hope everything's okay.

02:45.641 --> 02:48.675
Thank you.

02:50.712 --> 02:53.113
What are you doing
in my home?

02:53.115 --> 02:55.682
I'm here because I have a way
to get your Renoir back,

02:55.684 --> 02:57.350
but I'm gonna need something
from you.

02:57.352 --> 02:59.252
- And what exactly is that?
- Give your ex the villa

02:59.254 --> 03:01.588
in Bordeaux, and guarantee
she never pays a nickel

03:01.590 --> 03:03.890
of upkeep.
- And why would I do that?

03:03.892 --> 03:05.692
Because you asked me
to get that painting back

03:05.694 --> 03:07.327
and this is the only way
that's gonna happen.

03:07.329 --> 03:08.962
No, I mean
why would I do that

03:08.964 --> 03:11.531
when your firm is about
to sign my biggest competitor?

03:11.533 --> 03:13.667
- What are you talking about?
- I just learned

03:13.669 --> 03:15.502
Samantha Wheeler's about
to sign Delta.

03:15.504 --> 03:16.937
- God damn it.
- See, I thought

03:16.939 --> 03:18.672
I made it clear
that if I sign with you

03:18.674 --> 03:20.273
it is because I trust you.

03:20.275 --> 03:22.275
Using me as a stalking horse
doesn't make me feel like

03:22.277 --> 03:23.710
I can trust you.
- Gavin, that's not

03:23.712 --> 03:25.445
what's going on here.
- I told you,

03:25.447 --> 03:27.614
that painting
is personal to me.

03:27.616 --> 03:29.549
I'm gonna tell you why.

03:29.551 --> 03:31.184
My father was not
a wealthy man,

03:31.186 --> 03:33.253
but he had an education.

03:33.255 --> 03:34.721
If there's one thing
he appreciated

03:34.723 --> 03:37.490
more than anything, it was art.

03:37.492 --> 03:39.326
Every Sunday, we'd go
to a different gallery.

03:39.328 --> 03:40.860
We'd walk through--
he would tell me

03:40.862 --> 03:43.296
everything he knew
about every painting there was.

03:43.298 --> 03:45.298
You know who
his favorite artist was?

03:45.300 --> 03:46.967
Renoir.

03:46.969 --> 03:48.969
I paid $8 million
for that painting.

03:48.971 --> 03:52.472
It's worth twice that now,
but I would never sell it...

03:52.474 --> 03:57.777
because every time
I look at it...

03:57.779 --> 03:59.646
I think of him.

03:59.648 --> 04:02.382
Gavin, I told you
I'll get that painting back

04:02.384 --> 04:03.583
and I will.

04:03.585 --> 04:05.085
And I'll tell you
something else--

04:05.087 --> 04:06.620
There's no way
Samantha Wheeler's signing

04:06.622 --> 04:08.788
Delta goddamn Airlines.

04:11.994 --> 04:14.094
Thanks.

04:14.096 --> 04:16.730
Alex, what a pleasant surprise.

04:16.732 --> 04:18.298
Cut the bullshit.

04:18.300 --> 04:20.100
I just found out you're going
after Delta Airlines.

04:20.101 --> 04:21.901
Not just going after,
it's practically a done deal.

04:21.903 --> 04:24.104
That was fast,
since you only talked to Delta

04:24.106 --> 04:26.172
after you found out
I was pursuing Gavin Andrews.

04:26.174 --> 04:27.641
One had nothing
to do with the other.

04:27.643 --> 04:29.743
And I said cut the bullshit.

04:29.745 --> 04:32.145
You did this because you knew
you'd either sign Delta

04:32.147 --> 04:34.414
and I'd be out in the cold,
or Gavin Andrews

04:34.416 --> 04:36.283
would accuse me of using him
as a stalking horse

04:36.285 --> 04:38.685
and I'd be out in the cold.
- If you're so sure of that,

04:38.687 --> 04:40.287
then what are you doing
standing here

04:40.289 --> 04:42.188
ruining my morning bagel?
- I'm here to tell you

04:42.190 --> 04:43.556
to back the hell off.

04:43.558 --> 04:44.391
Well, that's not
gonna happen.

04:44.393 --> 04:45.425
Listen to me.

04:45.427 --> 04:46.493
I don't know
how you did things before,

04:46.495 --> 04:48.762
but around here,
we don't stab each other

04:48.764 --> 04:49.996
in the back.
- Then what do you call

04:49.998 --> 04:52.499
going after my old client
for the sole purpose

04:52.501 --> 04:54.868
of making me look bad?

04:54.870 --> 04:56.703
Because I'm not gonna
let that slide.

04:56.705 --> 04:58.805
Not to mention I warned you

04:58.807 --> 05:00.206
Gavin Andrews
isn't worth the trouble.

05:00.208 --> 05:01.174
You don't want to look bad,

05:01.176 --> 05:02.575
or the client's
too much trouble?

05:02.577 --> 05:04.344
Which one is it?
- It's both,

05:04.346 --> 05:06.146
and if you can't see that
then it's not my problem.

05:06.148 --> 05:09.349
What I see is you standing
between me and a client,

05:09.351 --> 05:11.985
and if I were you, I'd get
the hell out of the way.

05:11.987 --> 05:13.687
Well, then you'd better
sign your guy fast,

05:13.689 --> 05:15.155
because I'm already on
the one-yard line with mine

05:15.157 --> 05:17.761
and I'm about to punch it in.

